    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think I'd rather see this as a metadata translation step in http_server.c\nthat rewrites host to :authority.\n\nOn Fri, Mar 13, 2015, 00:17 Tatsuhiro Tsujikawa notifications@github.com\nwrote:\n\n> \":authority\" is not mandatory in HTTP/2 unless request method is\n> \"CONNECT\". If \":authority\" is not present, server should look for\n> \"host\" header field. This patch does not check method value, it is a\n> future TODO. This is a first step for GH-1022\n> \n> ## https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/1022.\n> \n> You can view, comment on, or merge this pull request online at:\n> \n>   https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/1025\n> Commit Summary\n> - Use \"host\" header field if \":authority\" is not present\n> \n> File Changes\n> - _M_ src/core/surface/server.c\n>   https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/1025/files#diff-0 (6)\n> \n> Patch Links:\n> - https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/1025.patch\n> - https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/1025.diff\n> \n> â€”\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub\n> https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/1025.\n"
